1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,463
=Episode 23=
(Love Me till the Fan Stops Spinning)

3
00:01:46,098 --> 00:01:46,699
Xiaoming.

4
00:01:47,258 --> 00:01:48,538
Where were you last night?

5
00:01:48,738 --> 00:01:50,298
Why didn't you answer your phone?

6
00:01:50,458 --> 00:01:51,538
And you didn't come back.

7
00:01:51,699 --> 00:01:52,979
We were so worried about you.

8
00:01:53,538 --> 00:01:54,339
Yeah.

9
00:01:54,859 --> 00:01:56,298
My student has an upcoming exam.

10
00:01:56,458 --> 00:01:57,779
Her mom wanted me to tutor her.

11
00:01:58,258 --> 00:02:00,178
It got too late,
so I stayed at her place.

12
00:02:00,738 --> 00:02:03,098
Xiaoming, go get the money.

13
00:02:03,779 --> 00:02:04,378
What money?

14
00:02:04,579 --> 00:02:05,339
The scholarship.

15
00:02:05,458 --> 00:02:06,378
Xiaomi!

16
00:02:08,978 --> 00:02:10,899
What scholarship?
I didn't know about it.

17
00:02:11,019 --> 00:02:12,568
The National Motivational Scholarship.

18
00:02:13,858 --> 00:02:15,179
Didn't the teacher tell you?

19
00:02:23,378 --> 00:02:24,459
What's wrong with you?

20
00:02:25,299 --> 00:02:26,899
Why did you mention that to Xiaoming?

21
00:02:27,019 --> 00:02:29,418
It's not a real scholarship,
but financial aid for needy students!

22
00:02:29,418 --> 00:02:30,499
You really beat me.

23
00:02:31,138 --> 00:02:32,939
Is Xiaoming's family really poor?

24
00:02:33,219 --> 00:02:35,059
I heard she is
from a single-parent family.

25
00:02:35,418 --> 00:02:38,459
Her mom doesn't work,
and she has a sick younger brother.

26
00:02:48,658 --> 00:02:50,538
We've looked up
some relevant information.

27
00:02:50,538 --> 00:02:51,578
Education and English...

28
00:02:51,578 --> 00:02:52,299
Hello, Mr. Liu.

29
00:02:52,299 --> 00:02:53,138
There is a gap.

30
00:02:54,499 --> 00:02:55,679
Xiaoming, wait up!

31
00:02:55,899 --> 00:02:57,119
Alright, we'll talk later.

32
00:02:57,378 --> 00:02:58,059
What is it?

33
00:02:58,059 --> 00:02:59,098
Where are you going?

34
00:02:59,418 --> 00:03:00,619
To the Student Affairs Office.

35
00:03:00,818 --> 00:03:03,019
Student Affairs Office?
Can I help you with something?

36
00:03:03,019 --> 00:03:05,059
I want to give up
on the Motivational Scholarship.

37
00:03:06,698 --> 00:03:09,339
The scholarship is awarded
to eligible students by the faculty

38
00:03:10,219 --> 00:03:11,339
after an assessment.

39
00:03:13,059 --> 00:03:13,559
Right?

40
00:03:14,779 --> 00:03:16,578
It's just because
my family isn't that needy.

41
00:03:17,059 --> 00:03:19,538
I want to leave the opportunity
for those who need it more.

42
00:03:20,499 --> 00:03:22,739
Also, I can work part-time.

43
00:03:22,978 --> 00:03:24,779
I can earn money and support myself.

44
00:03:25,779 --> 00:03:27,378
Anyway, I want to cancel it.

45
00:03:28,179 --> 00:03:29,418
I have a job offer. Want it?

46
00:03:30,219 --> 00:03:30,818
Yes!

47
00:03:32,459 --> 00:03:34,138
Professor Zhuang
is doing a social survey.

48
00:03:34,339 --> 00:03:37,258
He needs someone
to help organize his materials. It pays.

49
00:03:37,619 --> 00:03:38,219
I'll do it!

50
00:03:39,138 --> 00:03:40,538
It's such a great opportunity.

51
00:03:40,739 --> 00:03:43,739
I get to participate in the project
with grad students and get paid.

52
00:03:44,219 --> 00:03:46,739
Most importantly,
Professor Zhuang will notice me!

53
00:03:46,939 --> 00:03:48,418
It'll help me apply for grad school.

54
00:03:48,818 --> 00:03:51,019
Sure, you're quite smart.

55
00:03:51,179 --> 00:03:53,538
Okay, if you're interested,
I'll just sign you up with him.

56
00:03:53,658 --> 00:03:56,059
Thank you, Mr. Liu.
I promise I won't let you down.

57
00:03:56,378 --> 00:03:56,878
That's okay.

58
00:03:57,258 --> 00:03:57,779
I'm leaving.

59
00:03:57,878 --> 00:03:58,378
Go ahead.

60
00:03:58,378 --> 00:03:59,019
Thanks, Mr. Liu.

61
00:04:12,138 --> 00:04:13,299
Annoying.

62
00:04:13,499 --> 00:04:14,179
Boring.

63
00:04:14,779 --> 00:04:15,899
It smells so good.

64
00:04:16,338 --> 00:04:17,018
Instant noodles.

65
00:04:17,458 --> 00:04:18,419
I got something for you.

66
00:04:28,338 --> 00:04:28,939
- For you.
- For you.

67
00:04:33,939 --> 00:04:36,018
We thought the same thing.

68
00:04:36,659 --> 00:04:37,778
Did you get paid?

69
00:04:39,179 --> 00:04:41,979
Why did you buy me a phone?
You should save money for yourself.

70
00:04:42,859 --> 00:04:43,619
What do you mean?

71
00:04:44,218 --> 00:04:46,378
I was supposed
to buy a TV set with the money.

72
00:04:47,179 --> 00:04:48,258
Don't be ungrateful.

73
00:04:49,739 --> 00:04:50,898
It's not even opened.

74
00:04:50,979 --> 00:04:52,979
Where did you buy?
The receipt? Let's return it.

75
00:04:52,979 --> 00:04:54,018
Return it? No way.

76
00:04:55,018 --> 00:04:55,672
Throw it out.

77
00:04:55,898 --> 00:04:56,739
What are you doing?

78
00:04:58,378 --> 00:04:59,818
I don't need a new phone.

79
00:05:00,059 --> 00:05:01,539
Your phone can't even take calls.

80
00:05:02,299 --> 00:05:03,258
I can't contact you.

81
00:05:03,578 --> 00:05:04,539
I'll just get it fixed.

82
00:05:04,619 --> 00:05:05,898
What's wrong with you?

83
00:05:06,578 --> 00:05:08,939
It's just a gift.
How did it become a problem?

84
00:05:09,218 --> 00:05:10,578
Can you stop buying me things?

85
00:05:10,659 --> 00:05:12,138
Then why did you buy me something?

86
00:05:26,419 --> 00:05:27,458
What's wrong?

87
00:05:27,859 --> 00:05:29,979
No need to be embarrassed. Be frank.

88
00:05:33,018 --> 00:05:33,859
Come on.

89
00:05:36,698 --> 00:05:38,099
Don't give me the silent treatment.

90
00:05:43,539 --> 00:05:47,018
I already accepted the phone.
I don't dare to treat you like that.

91
00:05:47,499 --> 00:05:48,979
Who gave me the courage?

92
00:05:49,578 --> 00:05:50,338
Thanks, boss.

93
00:05:50,979 --> 00:05:52,018
Want eggs in your noodles?

94
00:05:53,859 --> 00:05:54,359
No.

95
00:05:55,179 --> 00:05:55,679
How many?

96
00:05:55,698 --> 00:05:56,198
Get lost.

97
00:05:56,898 --> 00:05:58,299
Okay, no problem.

98
00:05:58,818 --> 00:05:59,659
You do your homework.

99
00:06:00,258 --> 00:06:00,898
Two eggs.

100
00:06:00,979 --> 00:06:01,619
Okay.

101
00:06:25,059 --> 00:06:26,739
(Later, He Yuqiong told me)

102
00:06:27,419 --> 00:06:28,499
(that from that day on,)

103
00:06:29,739 --> 00:06:31,258
(he became my burden.)

104
00:06:33,234 --> 00:06:37,725
(Qingzhou, 2023)

105
00:06:39,378 --> 00:06:40,258
About the tea set...

106
00:06:40,258 --> 00:06:42,499
After reconfirming with Mr. Liu,

107
00:06:42,778 --> 00:06:44,778
the antique tea set
is worth 180,000 yuan.

108
00:06:44,979 --> 00:06:46,939
It was a gift from Mr. Liu to Ms. Ren.

109
00:06:47,659 --> 00:06:48,818
Ms. Ren can keep it.

110
00:06:50,419 --> 00:06:54,778
Next, we can discuss something
regarding the joint funds.

111
00:06:56,338 --> 00:06:59,659
(Some souvenirs filled
with gratitude and affection)

112
00:07:00,138 --> 00:07:02,378
(are meaningless a few years later.)

113
00:07:03,939 --> 00:07:05,898
(And then on the opposite of that,)

114
00:07:06,578 --> 00:07:07,659
(some meaningless stuff)

115
00:07:08,258 --> 00:07:09,539
(Basement rental, Qingzhou, 2008)
(might become souvenirs.)

116
00:07:18,939 --> 00:07:20,859
Look, Mr. Liu is such a great guy.

117
00:07:21,778 --> 00:07:24,778
I didn't realize how significant
the project was until I joined them.

118
00:07:25,299 --> 00:07:28,698
He had one spot for the undergraduates.
Tons of students fought for it.

119
00:07:29,539 --> 00:07:31,499
If it weren't for him,
I wouldn't have secured it.

120
00:07:32,578 --> 00:07:33,378
He Yuqiong.

121
00:07:34,979 --> 00:07:35,818
He Yuqiong.

122
00:07:37,578 --> 00:07:39,739
I'm talking to you.
What are you writing?

123
00:07:40,619 --> 00:07:41,619
A love letter.

124
00:07:44,419 --> 00:07:47,499
We've been together for so long.
No need to write love letters again.

125
00:07:50,059 --> 00:07:51,739
It's not for you.

126
00:07:51,979 --> 00:07:52,859
Then who's it for?

127
00:07:53,138 --> 00:07:54,378
It's a secret.

128
00:07:54,698 --> 00:07:55,499
Fine.

129
00:07:56,778 --> 00:07:58,739
I doubt your writing level,
so I'm not interested.

130
00:08:01,338 --> 00:08:02,859
Someone else will be interested.

131
00:08:03,179 --> 00:08:05,138
I have a new team leader.

132
00:08:06,099 --> 00:08:07,179
My new leader is tall,

133
00:08:08,138 --> 00:08:09,939
with long legs,

134
00:08:10,458 --> 00:08:12,499
big eyes, and...

135
00:08:13,179 --> 00:08:13,979
What are you doing?

136
00:08:15,179 --> 00:08:16,179
What are you hiding?

137
00:08:17,299 --> 00:08:17,939
Move!

138
00:08:18,218 --> 00:08:18,739
No way.

139
00:08:18,859 --> 00:08:20,059
- Move!
- No!

140
00:08:20,059 --> 00:08:20,659
- No.
- Hurry up!

141
00:08:20,898 --> 00:08:21,499
- Three.
- No.

142
00:08:21,859 --> 00:08:23,258
- Two.
- One.

143
00:08:26,659 --> 00:08:27,939
Fine, go find that tall person

144
00:08:28,138 --> 00:08:29,859
with long legs, big eyes,

145
00:08:29,859 --> 00:08:30,698
and big breasts.

146
00:08:30,698 --> 00:08:31,258
I'm leaving.

147
00:08:31,378 --> 00:08:32,698
I'll show you.

148
00:08:33,698 --> 00:08:35,899
I didn't say big breasts.
Just look at it.

149
00:08:38,130 --> 00:08:39,698
(Budget)

150
00:08:40,498 --> 00:08:41,259
What is it?

151
00:08:44,539 --> 00:08:45,978
Rotating sausage grill machine.

152
00:08:47,379 --> 00:08:48,618
What kind of woman

153
00:08:48,618 --> 00:08:50,218
would like a love letter about this?

154
00:08:51,899 --> 00:08:52,498
Sit down.

155
00:08:55,578 --> 00:08:56,458
Help me calculate.

156
00:08:56,779 --> 00:08:57,458
Look,

157
00:08:58,098 --> 00:09:00,179
a sausage costs less than one yuan,

158
00:09:00,299 --> 00:09:02,379
while a grilled sausage
sells for three yuan.

159
00:09:02,738 --> 00:09:04,659
If I make a portable sausage machine

160
00:09:04,659 --> 00:09:07,498
with a battery,
I can set up a stall after work.

161
00:09:07,939 --> 00:09:10,498
I can sell 50 grilled sausages a day.

162
00:09:11,738 --> 00:09:13,098
Then I can make nearly 100 yuan.

163
00:09:13,299 --> 00:09:16,299
In thirty days, that matches my salary.

164
00:09:16,818 --> 00:09:18,738
Am I a business genius?

165
00:09:21,698 --> 00:09:23,578
You're just like my mom.

166
00:09:23,779 --> 00:09:25,139
You two should team up.

167
00:09:25,259 --> 00:09:26,738
My mom always daydreams,

168
00:09:26,818 --> 00:09:29,139
and it always ends up
losing more than gaining.

169
00:09:30,379 --> 00:09:31,539
Listen, Ren Xiaoming,

170
00:09:31,539 --> 00:09:34,098
I'll earn more money than you imagine.

171
00:09:34,539 --> 00:09:35,098
Alright.

172
00:09:40,059 --> 00:09:41,218
Then tell me.

173
00:09:42,498 --> 00:09:43,858
Tell me about the tall girl.

174
00:09:46,059 --> 00:09:48,659
What? Oh, you mean Mr. Li?

175
00:09:49,179 --> 00:09:49,738
Mister?

176
00:09:52,019 --> 00:09:55,139
Can't a guy have long legs and big eyes?

177
00:09:55,458 --> 00:09:57,978
You are biased!

178
00:09:59,738 --> 00:10:02,698
You're hitting a future business genius!

179
00:10:04,059 --> 00:10:04,858
Stop it!

180
00:10:05,259 --> 00:10:06,338
I'll fight back!

181
00:10:06,338 --> 00:10:07,139
Ouch!

182
00:10:08,218 --> 00:10:09,059
Scared now?

183
00:10:10,659 --> 00:10:14,458
Alright, get up, business tycoon.

184
00:10:15,019 --> 00:10:15,698
Hurry up.

185
00:10:15,779 --> 00:10:16,659
I'm not done.

186
00:10:16,779 --> 00:10:17,818
Get up.

187
00:10:17,818 --> 00:10:18,498
It hurts!

188
00:10:20,379 --> 00:10:21,738
Please, sit.

189
00:10:22,659 --> 00:10:23,419
Come on.

190
00:10:26,338 --> 00:10:28,218
I need to take good care of you.

191
00:10:28,698 --> 00:10:30,139
Who knows what will happen?

192
00:10:30,419 --> 00:10:32,019
When you're rich,

193
00:10:32,259 --> 00:10:34,299
you buy me my big house
with a big swimming pool

194
00:10:34,379 --> 00:10:37,019
and a private jet.

195
00:10:38,218 --> 00:10:41,019
Mr. He, please have some water.

196
00:10:41,419 --> 00:10:43,218
So pragmatic.

197
00:10:43,539 --> 00:10:45,259
Now I get a seat at the table.

198
00:10:52,338 --> 00:10:55,779
You dummy, do your thing. Hurry up.

199
00:11:12,698 --> 00:11:15,458
(With a house, we can buy a bed,)

200
00:11:15,818 --> 00:11:17,539
(an extra-large bed,)

201
00:11:18,019 --> 00:11:20,139
(the kind you sink right into
when you lie down.)

202
00:11:21,578 --> 00:11:24,259
(With a house, we can buy a cabinet,)

203
00:11:24,659 --> 00:11:27,379
(a very big cabinet
that can hold a lot of stuff.)

204
00:11:27,858 --> 00:11:29,939
(A cabinet just for her.)

205
00:11:30,994 --> 00:11:35,659
(Qingzhou, 2023)

206
00:11:35,659 --> 00:11:36,818
So, Mr. Liu?

207
00:11:37,618 --> 00:11:40,578
Are you satisfied
with the property division?

208
00:11:42,098 --> 00:11:44,218
It's just part of a pre-trial procedure.

209
00:11:44,858 --> 00:11:46,539
It doesn't mean we're divorcing.

210
00:11:46,818 --> 00:11:48,738
Then there is nothing to talk about.

211
00:11:50,458 --> 00:11:52,578
Have you forgotten the promise we made

212
00:11:54,379 --> 00:11:55,738
when we got married?

213
00:12:03,954 --> 00:12:08,306
(Basement rental, Qingzhou, 2008)

214
00:12:17,978 --> 00:12:20,618
Shouldn't you thank me
for buying this fan?

215
00:12:21,858 --> 00:12:23,259
Does it feel good?

216
00:12:23,738 --> 00:12:25,659
Sure, thank you.

217
00:12:26,259 --> 00:12:28,498
This fan's been spinning
for 100 years. It still works.

218
00:12:29,218 --> 00:12:30,939
Don't you think it's a magic fan?

219
00:12:31,218 --> 00:12:34,779
100 years is not that long.
It's just a mundane thing.

220
00:12:37,738 --> 00:12:39,019
What are you doing?

221
00:12:39,379 --> 00:12:40,858
Can we be together for 100 years?

222
00:12:41,659 --> 00:12:44,179
Why don't you ask
if we can even live for 100 years?

223
00:12:44,299 --> 00:12:46,019
Why couldn't we live to 100?

224
00:12:48,578 --> 00:12:49,218
100 years!

225
00:12:49,218 --> 00:12:51,779
What are you yelling for? Just shut up.

226
00:12:56,379 --> 00:12:58,379
Do you think true love really exists?

227
00:13:06,419 --> 00:13:07,939
Then what counts as true love?

228
00:13:09,019 --> 00:13:10,179
Lasting love.

229
00:13:10,738 --> 00:13:11,939
Lasting love?

230
00:13:13,939 --> 00:13:14,578
Okay.

231
00:13:15,419 --> 00:13:16,578
You're always like this.

232
00:13:27,299 --> 00:13:27,818
It stopped.

233
00:13:33,259 --> 00:13:34,338
This shabby...

234
00:13:34,338 --> 00:13:36,098
What kind of wiring is this?

235
00:13:36,539 --> 00:13:37,978
Did it get heatstroke?

236
00:13:38,139 --> 00:13:40,019
It's overheated. I'll fan it.

237
00:13:40,379 --> 00:13:43,098
It's awfully hot.
Let me have some breeze.

238
00:13:43,578 --> 00:13:44,578
Move over there.

239
00:13:44,779 --> 00:13:46,299
Could you let me have some breeze?

240
00:13:47,299 --> 00:13:48,299
Okay, go ahead.

241
00:13:49,218 --> 00:13:50,419
Let me have it.

242
00:13:51,899 --> 00:13:52,779
I'm dying of heat.

243
00:13:56,818 --> 00:13:58,858
Do you dare to make a bet with the fan?

244
00:14:00,498 --> 00:14:01,179
On what?

245
00:14:01,179 --> 00:14:02,818
Love me till it stops spinning.

246
00:14:05,618 --> 00:14:06,858
I get it now.

247
00:14:07,659 --> 00:14:09,818
You are trying to tell me

248
00:14:10,179 --> 00:14:12,299
that the fan can't break on a hot day.

249
00:14:12,939 --> 00:14:13,899
Fine.

250
00:14:14,299 --> 00:14:15,498
I'll learn how to fix fans.

251
00:14:15,498 --> 00:14:16,738
Are you kidding?

252
00:14:18,019 --> 00:14:19,659
You never took loving me seriously.

253
00:14:20,299 --> 00:14:21,578
Have you ever seen someone

254
00:14:21,578 --> 00:14:23,618
who treats dating like a serious job?

255
00:14:23,618 --> 00:14:24,858
Who's paying the salary then?

256
00:14:29,939 --> 00:14:30,738
What?

257
00:14:34,698 --> 00:14:36,259
I won't let the fan stop spinning.

258
00:14:52,299 --> 00:14:54,299
(Qidaohezi, 2023)
Think again if we miss any information.

259
00:14:54,338 --> 00:14:55,098
Got it, Ma'am.

260
00:14:55,098 --> 00:14:55,779
Captain Li.

261
00:14:56,858 --> 00:14:59,338
We found that Zhang Fang
changed his name after the car crash.

262
00:15:00,019 --> 00:15:02,779
No wonder Bai Shu had no idea
where he was all these years.

263
00:15:03,179 --> 00:15:04,978
Why do you think
Zhang Fang changed his name?

264
00:15:06,299 --> 00:15:07,019
(Zhang Fang, who changed his name)
What year was the accident?

265
00:15:07,539 --> 00:15:08,738
2008.

266
00:15:10,659 --> 00:15:13,858
(La City, 2008)
I could never get tired of this food.

267
00:15:19,498 --> 00:15:20,498
So good.

268
00:15:21,698 --> 00:15:23,659
You stay at the guesthouse
for a few days.

269
00:15:24,578 --> 00:15:25,458
I have a job to do.

270
00:15:25,738 --> 00:15:26,419
Where?

271
00:15:27,179 --> 00:15:28,098
Qidaohezi.

272
00:15:31,419 --> 00:15:33,218
Don't worry. I'll be quick.

273
00:15:33,779 --> 00:15:36,184
When I get back, let's go
to see the Northern Lights in Mohe.

274
00:15:39,899 --> 00:15:42,019
Then you have to
promise me no night driving.

275
00:15:42,858 --> 00:15:44,098
No drowsy driving.

276
00:15:45,498 --> 00:15:46,299
Be safe.

277
00:15:48,498 --> 00:15:50,539
You too. Don't go out at night.

278
00:15:56,498 --> 00:15:56,998
Here.

279
00:15:59,179 --> 00:15:59,698
What is it?

280
00:16:05,218 --> 00:16:06,019
For me?

281
00:16:07,139 --> 00:16:07,779
Be safe.

282
00:16:10,858 --> 00:16:11,698
Let's eat.

283
00:16:15,858 --> 00:16:16,698
Be careful.

284
00:16:16,818 --> 00:16:17,498
(Wholesale Flour)
Okay.

285
00:16:40,338 --> 00:16:41,259
Madam.

286
00:16:43,019 --> 00:16:44,338
I've been waiting for you.

287
00:16:47,259 --> 00:16:48,139
Where's Bai Shu?

288
00:16:49,698 --> 00:16:50,618
She's fine.

289
00:16:51,578 --> 00:16:53,779
You two must be tired

290
00:16:54,978 --> 00:16:55,818
after the journey.

291
00:16:56,259 --> 00:16:56,759
Not tired.

292
00:16:58,978 --> 00:17:00,818
I made her laugh the whole way.

293
00:17:01,618 --> 00:17:02,939
We are

294
00:17:03,858 --> 00:17:04,819
pretty happy.

295
00:17:09,819 --> 00:17:11,698
I allow you two to be together.

296
00:17:16,619 --> 00:17:17,419
Thank you, Madam.

297
00:17:18,698 --> 00:17:19,859
We're just friends.

298
00:17:20,619 --> 00:17:22,419
But I have one condition.

299
00:17:25,018 --> 00:17:26,218
Bring her back.

300
00:17:27,859 --> 00:17:29,139
Take her back home.

301
00:17:32,179 --> 00:17:35,339
How about I find you a good job?

302
00:17:37,179 --> 00:17:37,859
Madam.

303
00:17:39,859 --> 00:17:40,738
Bai Shu

304
00:17:42,018 --> 00:17:43,058
doesn't want to come back.

305
00:17:45,218 --> 00:17:47,579
Don't worry. She's really doing well.

306
00:17:48,339 --> 00:17:49,698
I'll take good care of her.

307
00:17:52,099 --> 00:17:53,258
You take care of her?

308
00:17:57,298 --> 00:17:58,859
I am her mother!

309
00:18:00,538 --> 00:18:02,419
Why should you be the one
to take care of her?

310
00:18:05,659 --> 00:18:07,018
Give Bai Shu back to me.

311
00:18:08,778 --> 00:18:09,419
Madam.

312
00:18:11,139 --> 00:18:12,419
Let me tell you the truth.

313
00:18:13,218 --> 00:18:14,218
As long as I'm with her,

314
00:18:15,659 --> 00:18:17,859
I won't let you lock Bai Shu up again.

315
00:18:19,139 --> 00:18:19,819
You go.

316
00:19:04,778 --> 00:19:07,859
It's okay if she doesn't come back.
Take good care of Bai Shu for me.

317
00:19:09,179 --> 00:19:10,659
This is her favorite snack.

318
00:19:11,458 --> 00:19:12,339
Please give it to her.

319
00:19:17,139 --> 00:19:17,738
Madam.

320
00:19:19,258 --> 00:19:22,058
Bai Shu is now my only family
in this world.

321
00:19:22,859 --> 00:19:24,440
She's more important than my life.

322
00:19:24,738 --> 00:19:25,659
I'll treat her well.

323
00:19:28,058 --> 00:19:28,698
Oh,

324
00:19:30,619 --> 00:19:31,819
leave me your phone number.

325
00:19:32,018 --> 00:19:35,018
If you want to ask about Bai Shu,
just give me a call.

326
00:19:41,859 --> 00:19:42,498
In a few years,

327
00:19:44,258 --> 00:19:45,538
if Bai Shu wants to come back,

328
00:19:46,579 --> 00:19:47,819
we'll both come visit you.

329
00:19:50,379 --> 00:19:51,099
Alright.

330
00:19:55,738 --> 00:19:57,939
Leave the snack bags open,

331
00:19:58,298 --> 00:19:59,738
or the snack might spoil.

332
00:20:08,659 --> 00:20:09,339
Madam.

333
00:20:10,179 --> 00:20:10,859
I'm leaving.

334
00:21:16,018 --> 00:21:16,659
- Hourly Reception Room
- Hello.

335
00:21:16,659 --> 00:21:17,538
- is hourly.
- Excuse me?

336
00:21:17,538 --> 00:21:18,778
- Which ward is Zhang Fang in?
- Nurse station.

337
00:21:18,939 --> 00:21:20,139
And one more thing...

338
00:21:20,139 --> 00:21:20,859
Excuse me.

339
00:21:26,538 --> 00:21:27,619
What are you doing here?

340
00:21:29,058 --> 00:21:30,778
I transferred Zhang Fang here.

341
00:21:32,579 --> 00:21:35,978
He just had surgery
and is out of danger.

342
00:21:58,258 --> 00:22:00,258
Zhang Fang.

343
00:22:00,738 --> 00:22:01,859
Zhang Fang, wake up!

344
00:22:02,099 --> 00:22:03,498
The anesthesia hasn't worn off yet.

345
00:22:04,619 --> 00:22:05,659
Let him sleep for a while.

346
00:22:07,058 --> 00:22:08,659
How did you know he was in a car crash?

347
00:22:11,218 --> 00:22:14,419
He came to see me,
and I gave him my phone number.

348
00:22:15,018 --> 00:22:17,778
The traffic police called me.

349
00:22:18,458 --> 00:22:20,058
Why did he go to see you?

350
00:22:20,579 --> 00:22:21,738
Why did he have your number?

351
00:22:25,778 --> 00:22:26,619
He said

352
00:22:27,859 --> 00:22:29,659
you and I are mother and daughter.

353
00:22:31,339 --> 00:22:32,379
Maybe one day,

354
00:22:34,139 --> 00:22:35,859
you'll want to make up with me.

355
00:22:37,579 --> 00:22:38,258
Impossible.

356
00:22:39,538 --> 00:22:41,139
I'll ask him myself when he wakes up.

357
00:22:44,738 --> 00:22:45,419
Here we are.

358
00:22:48,458 --> 00:22:49,258
This is Zhang Fang.

359
00:22:49,419 --> 00:22:50,738
How is Zhang Fang?

360
00:22:51,218 --> 00:22:52,498
The surgery went smoothly.

361
00:22:53,698 --> 00:22:55,218
I came to tell you

362
00:22:55,538 --> 00:22:57,778
that the car driver didn't make it.

363
00:22:59,419 --> 00:23:00,379
Officer.

364
00:23:01,018 --> 00:23:03,339
Zhang Fang always
followed traffic rules.

365
00:23:03,778 --> 00:23:05,339
How could he possibly have an accident?

366
00:23:05,538 --> 00:23:07,298
We're still
investigating the cause of it.

367
00:23:08,579 --> 00:23:10,698
Notify us as soon as he wakes up.

368
00:23:11,099 --> 00:23:11,659
Okay.

369
00:23:12,579 --> 00:23:14,778
He can't leave the hospital
even after waking up.

370
00:23:15,579 --> 00:23:16,179
Understood.

371
00:23:40,498 --> 00:23:42,298
There is a fireworks factory over there.

372
00:23:42,419 --> 00:23:45,018
A colleague told me
they're testing fireworks today.

373
00:23:45,139 --> 00:23:48,058
Many of them are the same models
used in the Olympics.

374
00:23:57,258 --> 00:23:58,179
So big.

375
00:24:00,819 --> 00:24:04,258
So beautiful.

376
00:24:04,819 --> 00:24:06,538
Have you seen a movie?

377
00:24:06,738 --> 00:24:10,579
They stand like this,
saying, "You jump, I jump."

378
00:24:24,659 --> 00:24:26,179
Stop it.

379
00:24:26,439 --> 00:24:26,939
Stop it.

380
00:24:26,939 --> 00:24:27,659
Annoying.

381
00:24:27,659 --> 00:24:28,579
- Who allowed you to kiss me?
- Annoying.

382
00:24:28,579 --> 00:24:29,379
- Who allowed you?
- Who allowed you?

383
00:24:29,538 --> 00:24:32,018
- Why are you copying me?
- Why are you copying me?

384
00:24:33,218 --> 00:24:33,819
Get lost.

385
00:24:33,819 --> 00:24:34,899
- Get lost.
- Get lost.

386
00:24:43,442 --> 00:24:46,136
(Hospital)

387
00:25:02,058 --> 00:25:02,698
You're awake.

388
00:25:04,778 --> 00:25:05,778
You actually survived.

389
00:25:09,819 --> 00:25:11,258
But the doctor said

390
00:25:14,218 --> 00:25:15,778
your leg injury is serious.

391
00:25:19,058 --> 00:25:19,819
So I'll limp.

392
00:25:21,339 --> 00:25:22,298
It's nothing.

393
00:25:23,859 --> 00:25:26,939
Surviving a crash like this

394
00:25:29,018 --> 00:25:30,379
is already a stroke of luck.

395
00:25:32,859 --> 00:25:34,498
The person you hit died.

396
00:25:35,458 --> 00:25:38,218
You heard the police
about how liability is assigned.

397
00:25:39,698 --> 00:25:40,939
You won't be exempt.

398
00:25:42,139 --> 00:25:44,379
The deceased's family
accepts a private settlement.

399
00:25:45,139 --> 00:25:46,258
They want one million.

400
00:25:47,419 --> 00:25:50,179
Your transport company
didn't purchase commercial insurance.

401
00:25:50,659 --> 00:25:53,016
Compulsory traffic insurance
pays out a little part of it.

402
00:25:53,258 --> 00:25:55,058
Do you have the rest of the money?

403
00:25:58,218 --> 00:25:59,538
If Bai Shu knew,

404
00:26:00,939 --> 00:26:02,339
she would definitely help you pay.

405
00:26:05,538 --> 00:26:06,778
Where would she get the money?

406
00:26:10,939 --> 00:26:11,859
I absolutely would not

407
00:26:13,298 --> 00:26:14,419
let her handle this.

408
00:26:15,419 --> 00:26:17,179
Do you think she would sit on this?

409
00:26:35,099 --> 00:26:36,099
Don't get upset.

410
00:26:44,298 --> 00:26:45,619
I'll think of a way for you.

411
00:26:48,899 --> 00:26:49,698
You leave.

412
00:26:52,298 --> 00:26:53,179
As long as you leave,

413
00:26:54,139 --> 00:26:56,978
I'll handle the rest for you.

414
00:27:04,339 --> 00:27:06,139
Actually, I'm not helping you.

415
00:27:07,698 --> 00:27:09,058
I'm helping Bai Shu.

416
00:27:10,659 --> 00:27:13,579
I don't want her
to have a hard life later on.

417
00:27:18,978 --> 00:27:20,218
You lost your job,

418
00:27:21,099 --> 00:27:22,179
and your leg is crippled.

419
00:27:25,099 --> 00:27:26,819
You'll be a heavy burden to Bai Shu.

420
00:27:36,258 --> 00:27:37,498
As long as you leave,

421
00:27:39,619 --> 00:27:40,859
I'll pay the compensation.

422
00:27:45,099 --> 00:27:45,778
Also,

423
00:27:47,778 --> 00:27:49,139
I can promise you.

424
00:27:50,939 --> 00:27:52,538
I won't lock Bai Shu up anymore.

425
00:27:53,379 --> 00:27:54,579
She is free.

426
00:28:14,978 --> 00:28:15,579
Xiaoming.

427
00:28:16,458 --> 00:28:18,139
Xiaoming, the morning star is out!

428
00:28:18,978 --> 00:28:19,478
Xiao...

429
00:28:29,579 --> 00:28:30,099
Hello?

430
00:28:31,379 --> 00:28:31,899
Fang.

431
00:28:32,339 --> 00:28:33,579
Why are you calling me?

432
00:28:33,698 --> 00:28:35,579
Yuqiong, I killed a guy
in the car crash.

433
00:28:38,298 --> 00:28:38,939
What?

434
00:28:39,298 --> 00:28:42,018
Don't contact me or look for me.

435
00:28:42,659 --> 00:28:44,619
If Bai Shu doesn't tell Xiaoming
about this,

436
00:28:44,619 --> 00:28:46,258
keep it a secret, in case she worries.

437
00:28:47,458 --> 00:28:49,099
When you're free, go check on Bai Shu.

438
00:28:50,099 --> 00:28:51,538
You and Xiaoming take care.

439
00:28:52,458 --> 00:28:53,018
That's all.

440
00:28:54,179 --> 00:28:55,018
What do you mean?

441
00:28:55,298 --> 00:28:57,099
Zhang Fang!

442
00:29:02,379 --> 00:29:04,978
What are you yelling about?
What happened?

443
00:29:09,099 --> 00:29:10,258
What happened to Zhang Fang?

444
00:29:10,819 --> 00:29:12,579
Nothing, I just fell asleep.

445
00:29:12,899 --> 00:29:15,978
I probably dreamed about him.
Did I call out his name?

446
00:29:18,899 --> 00:29:20,339
It's dawn.

447
00:29:22,939 --> 00:29:24,579
You didn't wake me up.

448
00:29:26,018 --> 00:29:26,939
It's all your fault.

449
00:29:32,179 --> 00:29:32,939
Let's go then.

450
00:29:34,139 --> 00:29:35,298
I have class in the morning.

451
00:29:36,218 --> 00:29:36,819
Let's go.

452
00:29:38,379 --> 00:29:39,899
I have class in the morning.

453
00:29:40,579 --> 00:29:41,579
Put your clothes on.

454
00:29:41,579 --> 00:29:42,079
Okay.

455
00:29:43,298 --> 00:29:43,978
Let me help you.

456
00:29:44,579 --> 00:29:45,659
My leg is numb.

457
00:29:45,659 --> 00:29:47,179
You go first. I'll come down slowly.

458
00:29:47,659 --> 00:29:48,579
I'll go down first.

459
00:29:48,579 --> 00:29:49,179
Go ahead.

460
00:30:04,579 --> 00:30:07,179
Sorry, the phone you are calling
is powered off.

461
00:30:07,458 --> 00:30:08,819
The phone you are calling...

462
00:30:11,419 --> 00:30:14,018
Sorry, the phone you are calling
is powered off.

463
00:30:14,298 --> 00:30:16,458
The phone you are calling
is powered off.

464
00:30:22,354 --> 00:30:24,419
(Qidaohezi, 2023)

465
00:30:24,419 --> 00:30:25,218
- Captain Li.
- What did you get?

466
00:30:25,698 --> 00:30:27,579
This is the information
from the traffic office.

467
00:30:27,579 --> 00:30:29,899
On the civil side,
the accident was settled privately.

468
00:30:30,298 --> 00:30:31,139
On the criminal side,

469
00:30:31,379 --> 00:30:33,978
the dashcam shows
Zhang Fang wasn't driving fatigued.

470
00:30:34,139 --> 00:30:36,738
The other driver suddenly changed lanes
and shared responsibility.

471
00:30:36,859 --> 00:30:37,978
So no criminal charges.

472
00:30:38,498 --> 00:30:39,498
But after the accident,

473
00:30:40,298 --> 00:30:41,939
Zhang Fang vanished into thin air.

474
00:30:48,562 --> 00:30:50,712
(Car accident, disappearance)

475
00:31:01,339 --> 00:31:02,698
Do you know where Zhang Fang went?

476
00:31:04,218 --> 00:31:04,978
I don't know.

477
00:31:05,659 --> 00:31:08,579
Why did Zhang Fang leave
after the car accident?

478
00:31:10,099 --> 00:31:11,298
I also want to know

479
00:31:12,298 --> 00:31:15,419
if he chose to leave himself,
or if he was forced to leave.

480
00:31:16,859 --> 00:31:20,179
Didn't you try to contact Zhang Fang?

481
00:31:23,258 --> 00:31:24,778
He chose to leave me.

482
00:31:26,659 --> 00:31:30,258
When I had built trust with him
to face any difficulties together,

483
00:31:31,419 --> 00:31:32,379
he abandoned me.

484
00:31:35,139 --> 00:31:37,738
I was tired, but I still wanted to live.

485
00:31:38,538 --> 00:31:39,899
The cemetery was the right choice.

486
00:31:41,810 --> 00:31:45,592
(Rest Cemetery, Qidaohezi, 2008)

487
00:31:46,379 --> 00:31:47,778
(Ge Wenjun realized)

488
00:31:47,778 --> 00:31:50,978
(that only by giving me limited space
could she keep me.)

489
00:31:51,538 --> 00:31:53,978
(So she allowed me to move out.)

490
00:32:00,498 --> 00:32:02,179
(I got a job at Rest Cemetery,)

491
00:32:02,579 --> 00:32:04,298
(planning to stay there
for the rest of my life.)

492
00:32:08,859 --> 00:32:10,978
(If someone
gets used to being abandoned,)

493
00:32:11,579 --> 00:32:14,978
(doesn't she also have ample reason
to abandon herself?)

494
00:32:15,939 --> 00:32:18,579
(Betraying myself is easier
than persevering.)

495
00:32:20,018 --> 00:32:23,538
If Wang Hao hadn't come
to find me in the summer of 2010,

496
00:32:24,619 --> 00:32:28,218
I might have lived my boring life
as Bai Shu.

497
00:32:31,419 --> 00:32:33,258
In the summer of 2010,

498
00:32:34,619 --> 00:32:35,819
what exactly happened?

499
00:32:38,139 --> 00:32:41,698
Find the diary,
and you'll find out the truth.

500
00:32:44,698 --> 00:32:45,738
(Diary again?)

501
00:34:16,722 --> 00:34:21,362
(Contacts)

502
00:34:21,362 --> 00:34:29,304
(Qidaohezi Qidian Middle School Statue Case,
the latest clues surface one by one.)

503
00:34:43,410 --> 00:34:44,568
(Fu)

504
00:34:51,762 --> 00:34:56,562
(Huang Zhiqiang:
What exactly do you want?)

505
00:35:02,642 --> 00:35:06,092
(Jiashu: I knew it earlier.)
(Come quickly.)

506
00:35:39,922 --> 00:35:41,618
(6 Items Selected)

507
00:35:49,362 --> 00:35:51,768
(Permanently delete all items)

508
00:36:30,319 --> 00:36:31,379
(Same-Day Delivery)
Hello, it's your mail.

509
00:36:31,859 --> 00:36:32,538
Where is it from?

510
00:36:32,899 --> 00:36:33,658
It says an address.

511
00:36:35,819 --> 00:36:36,379
Thanks.

512
00:36:36,379 --> 00:36:36,879
No problem.

513
00:36:58,962 --> 00:37:01,144
(Breathe. I'm back.)

514
00:37:02,819 --> 00:37:05,058
(I'm back.)

515
00:37:09,682 --> 00:37:10,194
(Huang Zhiqiang)

516
00:37:21,554 --> 00:37:24,466
(Huang Zhiqiang)

517
00:37:25,939 --> 00:37:26,498
Hello?

518
00:37:28,379 --> 00:37:29,259
I'm back.

519
00:37:31,018 --> 00:37:32,458
Find me a place to stay.

520
00:37:34,458 --> 00:37:35,779
A place with internet access.

521
00:38:59,259 --> 00:39:02,538
Stay here for now
and don't contact anyone.

522
00:39:03,339 --> 00:39:04,219
Wait for my message.

523
00:39:09,538 --> 00:39:10,498
Turn it off.

524
00:39:16,339 --> 00:39:17,018
She...

525
00:39:19,458 --> 00:39:20,098
How's she?

526
00:39:22,538 --> 00:39:23,538
She is happy

527
00:39:24,939 --> 00:39:25,859
with a good life.

528
00:39:29,658 --> 00:39:31,578
She has a daughter named Xiaoyu.

529
00:39:32,859 --> 00:39:33,859
Xiaoyu is five years old.

530
00:39:45,899 --> 00:39:47,219
She doesn't look like Bai Shu.

531
00:39:48,299 --> 00:39:49,299
She takes after her dad?

532
00:39:50,259 --> 00:39:51,538
Is that any of your business?

533
00:39:52,299 --> 00:39:55,379
Don't come back again
without my instruction.

534
00:39:56,178 --> 00:39:57,219
And don't go find her.

535
00:39:59,339 --> 00:40:00,098
Okay?

536
00:40:10,118 --> 00:40:10,618
Well,

537
00:40:10,618 --> 00:40:12,219
I got everything you asked for,

538
00:40:12,779 --> 00:40:13,658
just as you requested.

539
00:40:16,219 --> 00:40:18,498
Don't go outside for no reason.

540
00:40:18,939 --> 00:40:20,379
There are too many eyes.

541
00:40:29,578 --> 00:40:30,098
Key.

542
00:40:54,538 --> 00:40:55,939
No rush. Drive carefully.

543
00:40:56,339 --> 00:40:58,616
We have time before the trial.
Let's go through it again.

544
00:40:59,158 --> 00:41:02,299
Liu Xiaoran is very likely
to present your chat logs

545
00:41:02,299 --> 00:41:06,178
and transaction records,
suggesting an affair of yours.

546
00:41:06,699 --> 00:41:09,779
He will claim you want a divorce
because you've cheated on him.

547
00:41:10,058 --> 00:41:12,739
How will you respond
to the chat logs in court?

548
00:41:13,379 --> 00:41:14,899
Just a very close friend.

549
00:41:16,219 --> 00:41:18,219
Okay, and the transaction records?

550
00:41:19,178 --> 00:41:20,739
That was my own money.

551
00:41:21,538 --> 00:41:23,098
I can spend it on whoever I want.

552
00:41:23,458 --> 00:41:24,819
I can spend it as I like.

553
00:41:25,859 --> 00:41:29,339
Luckily, those are not love messages.

554
00:41:29,618 --> 00:41:31,538
But think of
a more reasonable explanation.

555
00:41:31,859 --> 00:41:34,859
For example, if the family
of your friend needed your help.

556
00:41:34,939 --> 00:41:36,978
You were just helping him out.

557
00:41:37,498 --> 00:41:40,259
Liu Xiaoran doesn't
have any other evidence,

558
00:41:40,978 --> 00:41:41,498
does he?

559
00:41:44,219 --> 00:41:45,578
How should I know?

560
00:41:46,058 --> 00:41:48,458
But you at least know what you did.

561
00:41:56,699 --> 00:41:59,859
You're laughing now,
but the judge will make you cry later.

562
00:41:59,859 --> 00:42:01,939
He'll ask you if you have an affair

563
00:42:01,939 --> 00:42:04,138
or someone you flirt with.

564
00:42:04,978 --> 00:42:05,699
Does he

565
00:42:06,779 --> 00:42:08,219
actually exist?

566
00:42:12,339 --> 00:42:15,498
(It seems like from the very beginning,
I never acknowledged his existence.)

567
00:42:16,050 --> 00:42:20,018
(Qingzhou, 2008)

568
00:42:20,018 --> 00:42:21,939
(He Yuqiong has been
in Qingzhou for months.)

569
00:42:22,978 --> 00:42:25,018
(I haven't told anyone about him.)

570
00:42:29,538 --> 00:42:31,498
(I never introduced He Yuqiong
to everyone,)

571
00:42:31,939 --> 00:42:33,859
(not because I thought
he didn't belong here,)

572
00:42:34,859 --> 00:42:37,259
(but because I was just an onlooker.)

573
00:42:45,779 --> 00:42:46,899
I'm too tired.

574
00:42:46,899 --> 00:42:48,819
I even want to skip classes.

575
00:42:48,819 --> 00:42:51,339
Don't go back today.
Let's go to the night market.

576
00:42:51,538 --> 00:42:52,259
No.

577
00:42:52,259 --> 00:42:53,336
I have something to do.

578
00:42:55,618 --> 00:42:58,138
Tell me honestly.
Are you seeing someone?

579
00:42:58,458 --> 00:42:59,219
Tell us.

580
00:42:59,458 --> 00:43:00,739
- Are you?
- Are you?

581
00:43:01,699 --> 00:43:03,899
No, stop it.

582
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
